 A school bus on Saturday plunged into River Enziu in Kitui County
killing at least 22 people, among them four children. The bus, which was trying to cross a flooded bridge, was
overpowered by the waters and tripped over with passengers on board. The bus belonging to St. Joseph Seminary School in Mwingi is
said to have been moving from Mwingi town to Nuu ferrying church choir members
to a wedding function when tragedy struck. Confirming the incident, Mwingi East OCPD Joseph Yakan revealed
that the school bus had approximately 50 passengers on board at the time of the
incident.  Rescue operations are ongoing. 